This code sets up a simple client-server communication using sockets. The server listens for incoming connections on port 8080 and accepts a single client connection. The client connects to the server and sends a "Hello from client" message. The server receives the message, prints it, and sends a "Hello from server" response back to the client. The client receives the response and prints it.

